    <h2>Method</h2>

    <ol>
        <li>{{ dT() }} Preheat fan oven to 200‚ÑÉ, and boil kettle.</li>
        <li>{{ dT() }} Rinse the {{ tooltipAmount('lentils', 150, 'g') }} under cold running water, and add to a pot with {{ controlled(500) }}ml cold water. Bring to a boil and cook for 20-25 min, until tender; then drain and set aside.</li>
        <li>{{ dT() }} Cut the cauliflower into bite-sized pieces and put on a baking tray. Drizzle with vegetable oil and add salt and pepper. Bake for 20 mins.</li>
        <li>{{ dT() }} Meanwhile, finely slice the {{ tooltipAmount('onion', 1, '') }}, finely chop the {{ tooltipAmount('garlic', 2, 'cloves') }}, and chop the {{ tooltipAmount('carrot', 1, '') }} to 2cm pieces.</li>
        <li>{{ dT() }} Heat a large, lidded pan with {{ controlled(2) }}tbsp vegetable oil over medium heat. Once hot, add the onion, {{ tooltipAmount('ground coriander', 2, 'tsp') }} and {{ tooltipAmount('curry powder', 2, 'tbsp') }}. Cook for 2 mins before adding the garlic and carrots. Cook for 4 more mins until starting to colour</li>
        <li>{{ dT() }} Meanwhile, dissolve the {{ tooltipAmount('stock cube', 1, '') }} in {{ controlled(400) }}ml boiled water.</li>
        <li>{{ dT() }} Add the stock and {{ tooltipAmount('sultanas', 30, 'g') }} to the pan, cover and cook for 10 mins.</li>
        <li>{{ dT() }} Meanwhile, roast the {{ tooltipAmount('cashews', 30, 'g') }} for 5 mins or until starting to brown.</li>
        <li>{{ dT() }} Chop the {{ tooltipAmount('coriander', 20, 'g') }} finely, and chop the warm cashews coarsely.</li>
        <li>{{ dT() }} Remove the vegetables from the heat and stir in the drained lentils, {{ tooltipAmount('yoghurt', 150, 'g') }}, coriander and roast cauliflower.</li>
        <li>{{ dT() }} Serve and enjoy.</li>
